            "text": "To determine the maximum height the toy rocket reaches before it starts to descend, we need to analyze the given height equation:",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp1",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 129,
            "end": 159,
            "label": "restatement",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ h(t) = 200t - 4.9t^2 \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp2",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 159,
            "end": 248,
            "label": "restatement",
            "text": "This equation represents the height \\( h \\) of the rocket as a function of time \\( t \\). ",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp3",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 248,
            "end": 327,
            "label": "fact",
            "text": "The rocket reaches its maximum height when its vertical velocity becomes zero. ",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp4",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 327,
            "end": 454,
            "label": "planning",
            "text": "To find this, we first need to find the velocity function by taking the derivative of the height function with respect to time:",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp5",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 454,
            "end": 514,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ v(t) = \\frac{dh}{dt} = \\frac{d}{dt}(200t - 4.9t^2) \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp6",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 514,
            "end": 548,
            "label": "planning",
            "text": "Using basic differentiation rules:",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp7",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 548,
            "end": 575,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ v(t) = 200 - 9.8t \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp8",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 575,
            "end": 650,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "The rocket reaches its maximum height when the velocity \\( v(t) \\) is zero:",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp9",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 650,
            "end": 674,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ 200 - 9.8t = 0 \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp10",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 674,
            "end": 694,
            "label": "planning",
            "text": "Solving for \\( t \\):",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp11",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 694,
            "end": 778,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ 9.8t = 200 \\]\n\\[ t = \\frac{200}{9.8} \\]\n\\[ t \\approx 20.41 \\text{ seconds} \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp12",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 778,
            "end": 864,
            "label": "planning",
            "text": "Now, we substitute this time back into the height equation to find the maximum height:",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp13",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 864,
            "end": 910,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ h(20.41) = 200(20.41) - 4.9(20.41)^2 \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp14",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 910,
            "end": 932,
            "label": "planning",
            "text": "Calculating each term:",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp15",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 932,
            "end": 1010,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ 200(20.41) = 4082 \\]\n\\[ 4.9(20.41)^2 = 4.9(416.5681) \\approx 2041.18 \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp16",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 1010,
            "end": 1053,
            "label": "planning",
            "text": "Subtracting the second term from the first:",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp17",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 1053,
            "end": 1140,
            "label": "reasoning",
            "text": "\n\n\\[ h(20.41) \\approx 4082 - 2041.18 \\]\n\\[ h(20.41) \\approx 2040.82 \\text{ meters} \\]\n\n",
            "source": "response"
        },
        {
            "id": "resp18",
            "annotation": true,
            "start": 1140,
            "end": 1252,
            "label": "conclusion",
            "text": "Therefore, the rocket reaches its highest point at approximately **2040.82 meters** before it starts to descend.",
            "source": "response"
        }
